      "question": "If the $n^{th}$ term of an Arithmetic Progression is given by $a_n = 5 - 3n$, find the common difference $d$ and the sum of the first $10$ terms, $S_{10}$.",
      "answer": "$d = -3, S_{10} = -115$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Find the first two terms $a_1$ and $a_2$ by substituting $n=1$ and $n=2$ into the formula $a_n = 5 - 3n$.",
          "Calculate the common difference $d = a_2 - a_1$.",
          "Use the sum formula $S_n = \\frac{n}{2}(a_1 + a_n)$ or $S_n = \\frac{n}{2}(2a + (n-1)d)$ to compute $S_{10}$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$a_1 = 5 - 3(1) = 2 \\\\ a_2 = 5 - 3(2) = -1 \\\\ d = a_2 - a_1 = -1 - 2 = -3 \\\\ a_{10} = 5 - 3(10) = -25 \\\\ S_{10} = \\frac{10}{2}(a_1 + a_{10}) = 5(2 - 25) = 5(-23) = -115$"
      },
